Adams Oshiomhole, All Progressives Congress, APC National Chairman has threatened that Bukola Saraki, President of the Senate will be impeached if he failed to resign as the presiding Officer of upper chamber. Oshiomhole who gave this stated this Friday evening during a press conference at APC National Secretariat said, “If he does not resign, he will be impeached according to law and not by thuggery or by mob or anything that undemocratic. He cannot sustain a minority rule in the Senate and that is what is haunting him in the Senate. “When I say that the Senate President will be impeached, let me emphasise that he will be impeached properly according to law. The constitution is clear how a presiding officer can be impeached and because several impeachments has taken place, we are not about to witness what has not taken place before”. Details later… 